results.name: Lexicographically earliest permutation of the natural numbers such that in decimal representation the final digit of each term is distinct from the initial digit of the succeeding term.
comment: More than the usual number of terms are displayed, in order to show the difference between this and some closely related sequences. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Mar 13 2014
A130572 is the inverse permutation; A130573(n) = a(a(n));
see A130576 and A130577 for record values and where they occur.
